    "creditline": "Gift of Microsoft",
    "description": "Flat, black, tapering rectangular form (a); top third of hard plastic with narrow metal touch control band in center; bottom two thirds of matte black pliable silicone encasing a jointed body that can be bent into a curved form. Separate small, black,rectangular, plastic and metal USB transceiver (b) on underside, attached via magnet.",
    "justification": null,
    "gallery_text": "The mouse, a pointing device that aids in performing operations on the computer screen, has become an integral tool in the digital age. For years, the predominant design has consisted of a unit with one or more buttons and a scroll wheel. With the advent of mobile computing, portability and comfort have become increasingly desirable. The wireless Arc Touch mouse was designed with these criteria in mind. The lower portion of the body, which contains more than ninety parts, is jointed and flexible, allowing it to be stored flat for travel, and then bent into a curve to fit the hand when in use. The minimal, ergonomic design includes large buttons and a simple metal touch strip that replaces the scroll wheel. The jointed section is covered in a silicone sleeve that makes the instrument comfortable and easy to grip. The small transceiver that connects the Arc Touch to a computer is magnetically held in place on the mouse\u2019s underside.",
